features: TWIN BABY DOLLS: This set features a pair of 12" soft-bodied baby dolls boy and girl, each with their own personality and touch-activated sounds. Your child will have double the fun with this set of twin babies!

MAGIC BABY BOTTLES: Watch your child's face light up as they feed their twins with the magic disappearing milk bottles included in this playset. Baby dolls with bottle is the perfect way to encourage imaginative play and spark their creativity.

TALKS, CRIES & MAKES SOUNDS: Bring playtime to life with touch-activated sound effects triggered by gently squeezing the dolls' bodies. Each doll giggles, cries, whimpers, and babbles with adorable baby talk.

BABY DOLL CARE SET: Turn your child's playtime into a valuable teachable moment with this baby doll care set. They can learn the importance of nurturing and caring for others while having fun with their new baby dolls.

DOLLS FOR GIRLS: Whether at home or in the classroom, this twin baby dolls playset is perfect for encouraging imaginative play and fostering creativity. Kids will love taking care of their new baby dolls and creating their own stories with them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Darling dolls, but…
reviews.reviewText: I have two girls and a boy on the way, so it’s instruction time to prepare the girls for their new baby brother. So we thought baby dolls would be a good start. These are two sweet infant dolls with darling faces and a perfect size for a 3 year old +. But there are no directions for the dolls to make the baby noises that is advertised with the dolls on Amazon. I read everything on the package, the only tip off was a warning about the battery. I went back to Amazon and re-read the information. Nothing. So I took the clothes off the doll and unvelcroed the body. Out fell the small box that made the doll giggle, coo, and cry. There was a small tab that I pulled out (as a result of experience, not instruction) and still no sounds. I pushed on the top and finally I heard somewhat muffled cooing. At this point I decided the doll didn’t not need cooing/crying sounds for my two little girls to enjoy the baby dolls. In this world of everything being electronic, it’s ok to pretend. That’s what I did as a young girl. Pretend. My girls are loving the dolls and the doll bodies are softer without the plastic box inside the body. They came with two bottles, which are fun. I would still buy them again.
